Diagnostic.Title: Directive using non nécessaire
Remove unnecessary blank line.
Declare type inside namespace.
Add parentheses when necessary.
Make field read-only.
Remove unused member declaration.
Tests should include assertions
Diagnostic.Description: The rule targets test methods that lack an assertion and consist solely of an action and, optionally, a setup.

Diagnostic.Title: Opening braces should be spaced correctly
Diagnostic.Description: An opening brace within a C# element is not spaced correctly.

Diagnostic.Title: Closing braces should be spaced correctly
Diagnostic.Description: A closing brace within a C# element is not spaced correctly.

Diagnostic.Title: Prefix local calls with this
Diagnostic.Description: A call to an instance member of the local class or a base class is not prefixed with 'this.', within a C# code file.

Diagnostic.Title: Do not combine fields
Diagnostic.Description: Each field should be declared on its own line, in order to clearly see each field of a type and allow for proper documentation of the behavior of each field.

Diagnostic.Title: Do not combine attributes
Diagnostic.Description: Each attribute usage should be placed in its own set of square brackets for maximum readability.

Diagnostic.Title: Attributes should not share line
Diagnostic.Description: Each attribute should be placed on its own line of code.

Diagnostic.Title: Using directives should be placed correctly
Diagnostic.Description: A C# using directive is placed outside of a namespace element.

Diagnostic.Title: Elements should appear in the correct order
Diagnostic.Description: An element within a C# code file is out of order in relation to the other elements in the code.

Diagnostic.Title: Elements should be ordered by access
Diagnostic.Description: An element within a C# code file is out of order in relation to other elements in the code.

Diagnostic.Title: System using directives should be placed before other using directives
Diagnostic.Description: A using directive which declares a member of the 'System' namespace appears after a using directive which declares a member of a different namespace, within a C# code file.

Diagnostic.Title: Using directives should be ordered alphabetically by namespace
Diagnostic.Description: The using directives within a C# code file are not sorted alphabetically by namespace.

Diagnostic.Title: Const field names should begin with upper-case letter
Diagnostic.Description: The name of a constant C# field should begin with an upper-case letter.

Diagnostic.Title: Accessible fields should begin with upper-case letter
Diagnostic.Description: The name of a public or internal field in C# does not begin with an upper-case letter.

Diagnostic.Title: Variable names should not be prefixed
Diagnostic.Description: A field name in C# is prefixed with 'm_', 's_', or 't_'.

Diagnostic.Title: Field names should not contain underscore
Diagnostic.Description: A field name in C# contains an underscore.

Diagnostic.Title: Access modifier should be declared
Diagnostic.Description: The access modifier for a C# element has not been explicitly defined.

Diagnostic.Title: Fields should be private
Diagnostic.Description: A field within a C# class has an access modifier other than private.

Diagnostic.Title: Arithmetic expressions should declare precedence
Diagnostic.Description: A C# statement contains a complex arithmetic expression which omits parenthesis around operators.

Diagnostic.Title: Element should not be on a single line
Diagnostic.Description: A C# element containing opening and closing braces is written completely on a single line.

Diagnostic.Title: Braces should not be omitted
Diagnostic.Description: The opening and closing braces for a C# statement have been omitted.

Diagnostic.Title: Opening braces should not be followed by blank line
Diagnostic.Description: An opening brace within a C# element, statement, or expression is followed by a blank line.

Diagnostic.Title: Code should not contain multiple blank lines in a row
Diagnostic.Description: The C# code contains multiple blank lines in a row.

Diagnostic.Title: Closing braces should not be preceded by blank line
Diagnostic.Description: A closing brace within a C# element, statement, or expression is preceded by a blank line.

Diagnostic.Title: Single-line comments should not be followed by blank line
Diagnostic.Description: A single-line comment within C# code is followed by a blank line.

Diagnostic.Title: Closing brace should be followed by blank line
Diagnostic.Description: A closing brace within a C# element, statement, or expression is not followed by a blank line.

Diagnostic.Title: Single-line comment should be preceded by blank line
Diagnostic.Description: A single-line comment within C# code is not preceded by a blank line.

Diagnostic.Title: Elements should be separated by blank line
Diagnostic.Description: Adjacent C# elements are not separated by a blank line.

Diagnostic.Title: Elements should be documented
Diagnostic.Description: A C# code element is missing a documentation header.

Diagnostic.Title: File should have header
Diagnostic.Description: A C# code file is missing a standard file header.

Diagnostic.Title: Potential Command Injection vulnerability was found where '{0}' in '{1}' may be tainted by user-controlled data from '{2}' in method '{3}'.
Diagnostic.Description: The untrusted value passed to the command execution should be validated.

Diagnostic.Title: Potential XPath injection vulnerability was found where '{0}' in '{1}' may be tainted by user-controlled data from '{2}' in method '{3}'.
Diagnostic.Description: The untrusted value passed to the XPath query should be validated.

Diagnostic.Title: Potential Path Traversal vulnerability was found where '{0}' in '{1}' may be tainted by user-controlled data from '{2}' in method '{3}'.
Diagnostic.Description: The untrusted value passed to the redirect should be validated.

Diagnostic.Title: Give priority to scalar calculations over vector calculations
Diagnostic.Description: Scalar calculations are faster than vector calculations.
